original: Kewenter, Yngve, prakt, läkare, Göteborg, f. 3/7/97 i Sthlm av prof. Carl Filip Gunnar Andersson o. Anna Ta-bita Glasell. G. 28 m. Stina Wærn. Barn: Jan f. 30, Ulf 31, Göran 34, Eva 44. — Stud:ex. i Djursholm 16, med. kand. v. Karol. inst. 19 o. med. lic. där 26, med. dr i Lund 36. As’sist:-läk. samt e. läk. v. Stocksunds las. 23, vik. und:läk. v. Garn:sjukh. i Sthlm kir. avd. 24-25, e. o. aman. v. Maria sjukh. kir. avd. 26-27, bitr. läk. v. 34 Gbgs bariisjukh. kir. avd. 27-31, und:-läk. v. Hälsingborgs vanföreanst. 31-34, tf. överläk. där 34-35, e. o. aman. v. Lunds las. röntgenavd. 35, aman. v. Lunds las. ortoped. klin. 36, prakt, läk. i Gbg sed. 37. __Ba_t:läk. i Fik res. 26. Delt. s. friv. läk. i finsk-ryska vinterkriget tre mån. 39-40. Skr.: avh. o. upps. av liuv:sakl. ortoped. in-neh. FFrK4kl m sv, Dansk FrM.
translated: Kewenter, Yngve, MD, physician, Gothenburg, b. 3/7/1897 in Stockholm to Prof. Carl Filip Gunnar Andersson and Anna Tabita Glasell. M. 28 to Stina Wærn. Children: Jan b. 1930, Ulf b. 1931, Göran b. 1934, Eva b. 1944. — Graduated from Djursholm College in 1916, Medical Candidate at Karolinska Institute in 1919 and Medical Licentiate in 1926, Medical Doctorate in Lund in 1936. Assistant Physician and Resident Physician at Stocksund Hospital in 1923, Acting Assistant Physician at Maria Hospital Surgical Department in 1926-1927, Assistant Doctor at the Children's Hospital Surgical Department in Gothenburg from 1927 to 1931, Resident Physician at Hälsingborg's Rehabilitation Center from 1931 to 1934, Acting Chief Physician there from 1934 to 1935, Acting Assistant Physician at Lund Hospital Radiology Department in 1935, Assistant Physician at Lund Hospital Orthopedic Clinic in 1936, practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1937. Served as Naval Doctor in the Reserve in 1926. Participated as a volunteer doctor in the Finnish-Russian Winter War for three months in 1939-1940. Published papers and dissertations on scientific orthopedics. Awarded the Order of the Polar Star 4th class with a sword, and Danish Order of Freemasons.
